# Zephyr stack map: name  stack_size  peak_used  [priority]
# Derived from `CONFIG_THREAD_ANALYZER=y` console output on an nRF5340
# (Nordic Connect SDK). Zephyr reports "unused" high-water; we convert it
# to peak_used = stack_size - unused before recording here.
# Lower priority number = higher urgency (Zephyr cooperative threads use
# negative priorities; preemptible use >= 0).
main          2048   1180   0
sysworkq      4096   2620   -1
idle          320    96     15
logging       2048   1410   14
bt_rx         2048   1980   -8
bt_tx         2048   1024   -7
mpsl_work     1024   1010   -10
shell_uart    3072   1600   14
